      zPos - The z-coodrinate of the chunk.
      Returns:

    • getBiomeAt

      public int getBiomeAt​(int blockX, int blockY, int blockZ)
      Fetches a biome id at a specific block in this chunk. The coordinates can be absolute coordinates or relative to the region or chunk.
      Parameters:
      blockX - The x-coordinate of the block.
      blockY - The y-coordinate of the block.
      blockZ - The z-coordinate of the block.
      Returns:
      The biome id or -1 if the biomes are not correctly initialized.

    • setBiomeAt

      @Deprecated public void setBiomeAt​(int blockX, int blockZ, int biomeID)
      Deprecated.

    • setBiomeAt

      public void setBiomeAt​(int blockX, int blockY, int blockZ, int biomeID)
      Sets a biome id at a specific block column. The coordinates can be absolute coordinates or relative to the region or chunk.
      Parameters:
      blockX - The x-coordinate of the block column.
      blockZ - The z-coordinate of the block column.
      biomeID - The biome id to be set. When set to a negative number, Minecraft will replace it with the block column's default biome.

    • getBlockStateAt

      public CompoundTag getBlockStateAt​(int blockX, int blockY, int blockZ)

    • setBlockStateAt

      public void setBlockStateAt​(int blockX, int blockY, int blockZ, CompoundTag state, boolean cleanup)
      Sets a block state at a specific location. The block coordinates can be absolute or relative to the region or chunk.
      Parameters:
      blockX - The x-coordinate of the block.
      blockY - The y-coordinate of the block.
      blockZ - The z-coordinate of the block.
      state - The block state to be set.
      cleanup - When true, it will cleanup all palettes of this chunk. This option should only be used moderately to avoid unnecessary recalculation of the palette indices. Recalculating the Palette should only be executed once right before saving the Chunk to file.

      public void setDataVersion​(int dataVersion)

      dataVersion - The DataVersion to be set.
